      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "ModelSamplingSD3 settings",
      "properties": {
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "Node Parameters \n\n|Model| Parameter       | Default | Min | Max | Step |\n|-|-|-|-|-|-|\n|SD3| shift             | 3                | 0               | 100 | 0.01\n|WAN2.2| shift             | 3                | min 3               | max 10 | 0.01\n\nThese parameters allow users to precisely customize the model's sampling behavior. \nBest settings for WAN 2.2 shift 5-10.\n\n### Why this node\nThe node is essential for users seeking to refine model performance through enhanced control of sampling methods. This is especially useful in complex decision-making systems or any AI-powered applications that require a tailored approach to sampling.\n\n### Related Nodes and Differences\nWhile the ModelSamplingSD3 seems similar to other sampling nodes, its primary difference lies in its precision adjustment capability with the shift parameter, making it unique for cases requiring fine control over sampling strategies.\n"
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    },
    {
      "id": 105,
      "type": "MarkdownNote",
      "pos": [
        1689.4617919921875,
        -284.59521484375
      ],
      "size": [
        332.9522705078125,
        149.78750610351562
      ],
      "flags": {},
      "order": 17,
      "mode": 0,
      "inputs": [],
      "outputs": [],
      "title": "KSampler settings",
      "properties": {
        "ue_properties": {
          "widget_ue_connectable": {}
        }
      },
      "widgets_values": [
        "Since the standard sampler, unlike the KSampler (Advanced - return_with_leftover_noise), always generates noise and does not allow the process to be processed at any point (stat_at_step - mid point processes), and since it is not possible to specify the last step for processing, which allows control over the degree of refinement (end_at_step), but it should still be possible to generate randomized images, \n#### the seed of the first sampler is set to 0 and the seed of the second sampler is set to ‘randomize’."
      ],
      "color": "#432",
      "bgcolor": "#653"
    }
